               <msContents>
                  <summary>This papyrus appears to contain a hand-list of notes for a sermon on the cross in the tradition of the sermon De inventione sanctae crucis of Alexander Monachus (MG 87 III 4073 et sqq.). The text was perhaps meant to constitute an encomium to follow a discussion similar to that which precedes Alexander's encomium in De Inventione.</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Recto; Written across the fibers; scribe rotated papyrus 90 degrees to accommodate the format of the text.</note>
                     <note type="general">Location: Ann Arbor</note>
                     <note type="general">Pub. status: Recto; traces of writing on the Verso</note>
                     <note type="related">-</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
               </msContents>
